│ the false arm (ret %b). This corresponds to logic in InstructionSimplify's    │
│ simplifySelectWithICmpCond and simplifySelectWithEquivalence, which attempts  │
│ to use equality to substitute operands in select arms and if both arms        │
│ simplify to the same value, returns the false arm.                            │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ The function simplifySelectWithICmpCond applies equivalence-based             │
│ simplification for any ICmp eq, including pointer equality. Specifically, for │
│ Pred == ICMP_EQ, it calls simplifySelectWithEquivalence({{CmpLHS, CmpRHS}},   │
│ TrueVal, FalseVal,...). In the reproducer, Cond is icmp eq ptr %a, %b;        │
│ TrueVal is %a; FalseVal is %b. Substituting %a->%b causes both arms to        │
│ simplify to %b, and the code returns FalseVal (%b). This is unsound for       │
│ pointers due to provenance: choosing the other operand may change the pointer │
│ identity/provenance even if addresses are equal. The documentation comment    │
│ above simplifySelectWithEquivalence says it is intended for integer equality  │
│ or floating-point equivalence. However, the current code path incorrectly     │
│ uses it for pointer equality, because m_ICmp matches pointer compares too.    │
│                                                                               │
│ Therefore, we need to restrict the equivalence-based select simplification to │
│ integer (and FP in the separate FCmp path) but not pointer icmp eq.           │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ We will modify llvm/lib/Analysis/InstructionSimplify.cpp within               │
│ simplifySelectWithICmpCond to guard the equivalence-based substitution under  │
│ ICMP_EQ to only apply when the comparison operands are of integer type.       │
│ Concretely, before calling simplifySelectWithEquivalence for ICMP_EQ, add a   │
│ check to ensure CmpLHS->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(). If the type is       │
│ pointer (or non-integer), skip the equivalence substitution block.            │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit at llvm/lib/Analysis/InstructionSimplify.cpp lines ~4730-4760:           │
│ - Insert a type check guarding the ICMP_EQ equivalence simplification:        │
│                                                                               │
│ if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ) {                                              │
│   // Only perform equivalence-based substitution for integer compares.        │
│   Type *CmpTy = CmpLHS->getType();                                            │
│   if (CmpTy->isIntOrIntVectorTy()) {                                          │
│     if (Value *V = simplifySelectWithEquivalence({{CmpLHS, CmpRHS}}, TrueVal, │
│                                                  FalseVal, Q, MaxRecurse))    │
│       return V;                                                               │
│     if (Value *V = simplifySelectWithEquivalence({{CmpRHS, CmpLHS}}, TrueVal, │
│                                                  FalseVal, Q, MaxRecurse))    │
│       return V;                                                               │
│                                                                               │
│     // ... keep existing integer-specific patterns (|(X|Y)==0), (&(X&Y)==-1)  │
│ ...                                                                           │
│     Value *X;                                                                 │
│     Value *Y;                                                                 │
│     if (match(CmpLHS, m_Or(m_Value(X), m_Value(Y))) &&                        │
│         match(CmpRHS, m_Zero())) {                                            │
│       if (Value *V = simplifySelectWithEquivalence(                           │
│               {{X, CmpRHS}, {Y, CmpRHS}}, TrueVal, FalseVal, Q, MaxRecurse))  │
│         return V;                                                             │
│     }                                                                         │
│     if (match(CmpLHS, m_And(m_Value(X), m_Value(Y))) &&                       │
│         match(CmpRHS, m_AllOnes())) {                                         │
│       if (Value *V = simplifySelectWithEquivalence(                           │
│               {{X, CmpRHS}, {Y, CmpRHS}}, TrueVal, FalseVal, Q, MaxRecurse))  │
│         return V;                                                             │
│     }                                                                         │
│   }                                                                           │
│ }                                                                             │
│                                                                               │
│ - This ensures the equivalence-based substitution is not applied to pointer   │
│ equality conditions, avoiding the unsound select folding demonstrated by      │
│ Alive2.                                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By restricting simplifySelectWithEquivalence to integer equality within       │
│ simplifySelectWithICmpCond, we prevent incorrect simplification of selects    │
│ conditioned on pointer equality. The fix preserves intended behavior for      │
│ integer and floating-point cases while avoiding provenance-breaking           │
│ transforms for pointers. This should stop the erroneous replacement of select │
│ (icmp eq ptr %a, %b), %a, %b with %b and restore correctness under stricter   │
│ memory/provenance models.                                                     │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
